hopobject.body: What's the interest rate on this account? testoforce results Whatever the outcome of the upheaval at Lonely Planet, there is no doubt the traditional guidebook market is under intense pressure. Last year, AA Publishing confirmed it was no longer commissioning printed travel guides. In February this year, the trade magazine The Bookseller reported a 41 per cent decline in the travel print categories in the last five years, although it did highlight some “standout successes”, including the Lonely Planet guides to Thailand and Australia.
